  "narrative": {
    "intro": "HUBZone set-aside obligations totaled $359M in FY2026 to date, spread across 1,120 awards with an average award size of $321K. Obligations fell 60.9% year over year. Fiscal-year comparisons show a peak range from $938M to $1.1B in prior years and a current-year total of $359M for FY26. The Department of Defense accounted for the largest share of FY2026 to date obligations at $121M, followed by the Department of Homeland Security at $61.9M and the Department of Labor at $44.8M. The largest individual contractors in FY2026 to date include PANAMERICA COMPUTERS, INC. at $19.2M and T&H SERVICES, LLC at $19.1M. Other concentration areas include Other Computer Related Services at $104M and Other Technical and Trade Schools at $35.1M, indicating a significant portion of set-aside dollars in IT and training-related NAICS categories. These figures reflect partial fiscal-year totals and represent contract obligations recorded in the fiscal year to date.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "What changed year over year in HUBZone set-aside obligations?",
        "body": "Obligations fell 60.9% year over year. The FY2026 to date total is $359M compared with prior-year totals ranging from $920M to $1.1B in the FY21–FY25 period. This represents a notable reduction in obligations for the current fiscal year to date. Award volume in FY2026 to date is 1,120 awards with an average award size of $321K."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies and vendors dominate HUBZone set-aside awards in FY2026 to date?",
        "body": "The Department of Defense leads agency spending with $121M in obligations, followed by the Department of Homeland Security at $61.9M and the Department of Labor at $44.8M. The largest vendors are PANAMERICA COMPUTERS, INC. at $19.2M and T&H SERVICES, LLC at $19.1M, with FEDERAL RESOURCES CORPORATION at $17.2M and ANACAPA MICRO PRODUCTS, INC. at $16.8M also among the top recipients. Industry concentration is highest in Other Computer Related Services at $104M, with Other Technical and Trade Schools at $35.1M and Commercial and Institutional Building Construction at $31.5M."
      }
    ]
  },
